description: Jessie Diggins, age 32, won her first Olympic gold medal in 2018 in South Korea and has now captured two World Cup titles, blowing past European skiers who typically dominate cross-country skiing.
title: Jessie Diggins is a U.S. cross-country ski powerhouse after 2nd World Cup win

description: Troves of artifacts were stolen from Japan during the Battle of Okinawa in World War II. Over 20 pieces of looted items were found in the attic of a Massachusetts home.
title: A family found centuries-old Japanese art stolen during WWII in their attic

description: Known as 12P/Pons-Brooks, the rarely seen comet prone to colorful outbursts could soon be viewed without a telescope or binoculars.
title: The 'devil comet' is visible in the night sky, and is sticking around for the eclipse

description: How did the soda giant from America come to be seen as "local" in Africa? And what has the impact been on the continent for worse and for better?
title: Q&A: Author of 'Bottled: How Coca-Cola Became African' on Coke's surprising history

description: A volcano in Iceland erupted Saturday evening for the fourth time in three months, sending orange jets of lava into the night sky.
title: A volcano in Iceland is erupting for the fourth time in 3 months

description: President Biden was speaking at the annual Gridiron Club and Foundation Dinner, the first time he has attended during his presidency. Vice President Kamala Harris and other big names were there too.
title: Biden jokes that one presidential candidate is mentally unfit — and it's not him

description: Former President Trump claimed he will protect Social Security and warned of a "bloodbath" in the auto industry if he loses the election at a rally for Senate candidate Bernie Moreno in Ohio.
title: Trump says some migrants are 'not people', and warns of 'bloodbath' if he loses

description: Johnson studied with Ansel Adams in the 1940s and became known as one of the foremost photographers of San Francisco's Black urban culture.
title: Photographer David Johnson, who chronicled San Francisco's Black culture, dies at 97

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin is poised to extend nearly a quarter century of rule for six more years on Sunday after wrapping up an election that gave voters no real alternatives.
title: Russians cast final ballots in election preordained to extend Vladimir Putin's rule
